Merged PR 148104: Fix linter configs and rules

Fixed all linting issues and conflicts between prettier and stylelint by making a few changes:
- Default VSCode formatter is used for HTML.
- Stylelint is used for SCSS (and CSS in HTML).
- Added `.stylelintrc.json` which extends sass guidelines config and has some extra rules.
- Prettier is recommended for JS. Added some basic rules in `.editorconfig`.
- Removed all other prettier configuration and disabled it for html/scss.

Other notes:
- Ran linter after all that to fix formatting.
- Fixed stylelint vscode extension name. New extension works properly on save.
- Changed some line endings to LF.

- First public and stable release! 🎉
- Updated changelog with breaking changes

- Bumped minor version: 1.0.0 -> 1.1.0

Fix scripts in package.json (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#35)

yarn copy-files will now only copy README, LICENSE and CHANGELOG instead of all .md files (fixes iTwin/iTwinUI-react#34)

Updated @itwin packages:
- itwinui-css: 0.11.0 → 0.12.0
- itwinui-icons-react: 0.1.0 → 1.1.0
- itwinui-illustrations-react: 0.1.0 → 1.0.0

Initial table filter implementation with TextFilter.

Bumps itwinui-css to 0.13.0 for active filter class.

Add createComponent.js for automating boilerplate (#75)

`yarn createComponent [component]` will now write boilerplate files to component folder (and backstop folder) and append imports to barrel files.

Add Header and HeaderButton (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#45)

Added new `Header` component. Supports default and slim heights.

Also added subcomponents: `HeaderLogo`, `HeaderBreadcrumbs` and `HeaderButton`.

- Removed before/after tracks from non-default wizard steps.

Also updated icons-react (v1.1.1 -> v1.1.3) and illustrations-react (v1.0.1 -> v1.0.2) in lockfile.

message:
Update table classes from itwinui-css 0.20 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#135)

Bumped itwinui-css to 0.20.2 and updated all classnames.

Add 'warning' type to `StatusIconMap` and `Toast` (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#154)

- Added 'warning' type in StatusIconMap.
- Added CommonProps support in StatusIconMap (to allow using className in Alert and Toast).
- Added 'warning' category to Toast, and warning() function to toaster.
- Bumped itwinui-css to 0.21.0

Update tab styles using itwinui-css 0.22.0 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#172)

- Bumped itwinui-css from 0.21.0 to 0.22.0
- Updated class names and markup
- Added basic tabStripe logic
- Updated tests to pass

Release 1.10.0 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#183)

Release 1.9.0 → 1.10.0 + bumped itwinui-css to 0.22.1 for HorizontalTabs fix.

Update to itwinui-css 0.23.0 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#203)

Also added missing `.iui-fill` class to ProgressLinear

Update to itwinui-css 0.24.1 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#204)

Bumped itwinui-css, added class to menu item and updated tests.

- Removed all references to argType.defaultValue (deprecated).
- Added @babel/plugin-proposal-class-properties to main.js with loose: true to fix build error.
- Cleaned up UserIcon stories.
- Updated images.

message:
Add keyboard navigation to tabs (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#207)

- Added left/right arrow key navigation to tabs.
- Added focusActivationMode prop to toggle whether tabs should automatically be selected when focused.
- Renamed currentIndex to currentActiveIndex to prevent confusion with focusedIndex.
- Changed references of typeof and JSX.Element to use React.isValidElement instead.
- Bumped itwinui-css to 0.24.2.
- Misc cleanup.

Improve storybook UX (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#210)

Added storybook addon-essentials, replacing individual addons for docs, controls and actions. Includes new viewport and background switcher.

Renamed Story tab to Code.

Changed Docs tab to respect OS theme, and updated background color for non-inline stories.

Add head content (#193)

- Language is set to `en-US`.
- `<meta charset="UTF-8">` was added.
- SVG favicon is defaulting to .SVG, fallback is .ICO.
- Added Apple Touch icon.
- Added manifest & required images.
- Added Open Graph image.
- Most of this content is injected into the head of the minified HTML @ build time.

Bump storybook to 6.3.6 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#241)

Includes an important fix for undefined args. Also fixes Full Table story lagginess by not logging the full mouseenter event.

Update to itwinui-css 0.25.0 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#254)

Updated itwinui-css to 0.25.0.

- Added iui-text-spacing class to Typography components to preserve margins from before.
- Updated badge color to the new skyblue background.

Add jest-dom and upgrade jest + testing library (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#258)

- Added jest-dom and changed setupTests from js to ts (to transform ESM import for jest-dom).
- Moved setup to afterEnv
- Changed test environment to jsdom
- Upgraded testing-library and jest
- Fixed some tests

Update creevey and fix broken tests (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#264)

Bumped creevey to latest patch version and fixed broken tests/images.

feat: Split Header Button (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#256)

When user provides both onClick and MenuItems to Header button, header renders split header button.

chore: Update to itwinui-css 0.26 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#272)

Updated to itwinui-css 0.26.1 and made required changes in HorizontalTabs and Wizard.

feat(ExpandableBlock): use react-transition-group for animation (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#273)

Added CSSTransition classes for expand/collapse animation.
Updated to itwinui-css 0.27.0.

feat: Add new `VerticalTabs` component (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#278)

- Added new VerticalTabs component.
- Converted HorizontalTabs into a new internal Tabs component, with orientation prop.
- Deprecated HorizontalTab and renamed to Tab.

message:
feat(Wizard): Improve accessibility and forward ref (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#290)

- Added tabIndex and onKeyDown to clickable Steps.
- Changed aria-current=true to aria-current=step.
- Forwarded ref to allow user to modify aria attributes on any level.
- Updated itwinui-css to 0.27.3.

feat: Add Toaster improvements (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#276)

Adding placement props for Toaster.
Placement: top | top-start | top-end | bottom | bottom-start | bottom-end
Adding order prop for Toaster.
Order: descending (new toasts on top) or ascending (new toasts at the bottom).
chore(deps): Add mkdirp as a direct dev dependency (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#311)
feat(labeled-inputs): Add new layout options using grid (#287)
fix: updated typescript and eslint versions (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#319)

feat: Add `iconDisplayStyle` prop to LabeledInput and LabeledTextarea (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#309)

Added new iconDisplayStyle prop to LabeledInput and LabeledTextarea for hybrid layouts, and made all the other required changes based on iTwinUI-css 0.32.0. Preserved current behavior for message (i.e. not shown for inline displayStyle).

Also moved all common InputContainer logic into internal wrapper component.

chore(deps): Bump ansi-regex and replace ansi-html (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#350)

Force bumped ansi-regex and react-refresh-webpack-plugin, replaced ansi-html with ansi-html-community.
chore(deps): Updated ansi-regex and made audit to check only prod dependencies (#327)

feat(Alert): Add new `clickableTextProps` prop (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#357)

Deprecated onClick and added clickableTextProps to allow passing href. Updated class names using iTwinUI-css 0.34.0.

feat(SideNavigation): Add submenu support (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#376)

Added new submenu prop to SideNavigation, to be used with SidenavSubmenu component. Supports SidenavSubmenuHeader subcomponent. Uses react-transition-group helper for animation.

feat: Add new `ColorPicker` component (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#346)

Co-authored-by: bsteinbk <65047615+bsteinbk@users.noreply.github.com>
Co-authored-by: Mayank <9084735+mayank99@users.noreply.github.com>

chore: release 1.23.2 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#414)

Header: Fixed hover effects on header logo. (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#413) (0dae3ac)

style: Add prettier to lint-staged hook (#372)

Updated lint-staged to the latest version and added prettier-cli to run before stylelint on every commit. Ran formatter on all scss files.

chore(deps): Bump itwinui-css to 0.39.0 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#430)

Updated to iTwinUI-css 0.39.0. Made required changes in Tabs (switching from iui-tab-stripe div to CSS variables).

feat(Label): Add standalone `Label` component (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#431)

Added standalone polymorphic Label component to be paired with inputs.

chore: Add lint-staged to husky hook (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#458)

Added lint-staged v12 and upgraded husky to v4. Also locked down prettier to exact version.

chore: Bump itwinui-css to 0.41.0 and update buttons (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#466)

- Upgraded `iTwinUI-CSS` version to `0.41.0`
- Added `iui-default` class to default style buttons
- Updated `Header` screenshots to have 12px left margins in labels

chore(deps): Bump itwinui-css to 0.42.0 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#481)

Updated itwinui-css to 0.42.0 and made required changes in ButtonGroup and SplitButton (wrapping children with div).
fix(Table): Prevents from triggering sort when filtering (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#487)
feat(Table): Proper support for horizontal scroll (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#495)

chore: Bump autoprefixer to 10.4.1 (#434)

Bumped autoprefixer to allow using `@supports selector(:focus-visible)`. Also removed prefixed version of :autofill and bumped browserslist to match the version in autoprefixer.

feat: New focus styling (#166)

- Introducing a new focus mixin that uses outline & outline-offset instead of box-shadow.

Co-authored-by: Mayank <9084735+mayank99@users.noreply.github.com>

chore(storybook): Use webpack 5 and bump postcss to v8 (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#505)

Upgraded to webpack 5 which should depend on postcss v8. Force resolved the unused postcss v7 to v8. Fixes vulnerability in postcss v8.

Co-authored-by: Vykis <81580355+veekeys@users.noreply.github.com>

feat(Modal): Add full page modal (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#588)

Adds optional parameter `styleType`, that if set to "fullPage" displays the modal the size of the page. Adds animations to default and full page modals. Adds component `ModalContent` that should at minimum be used with full page modal content.

chore: Add Dockerfile with manual chrome install (#571)

Add a new Dockerfile which is a modified version of the one from backstopjs. A new buildDocker.js script is also added to package.json to build and load this image.
On CI, the image is built and cached using the docker/build-push-action.

Co-authored-by: Vykis <81580355+veekeys@users.noreply.github.com>

chore: Convert to monorepo (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#613)

Converted this repo into a monorepo using turborepo on top of yarn workspaces. Directory structure is split into apps/ and packages/.

- Moved all iTwinUI-react and config files into packages/
- Added a vite playground under apps/ which uses the linked itwinui-react package just for testing components in a more reliable setting compared to storybook.
- In the future, the documentation website folder will also live under apps/

lockfile was recreated so there were a lot of random changes I had to make for new deps, mostly in tests.

chore: release 0.56.0 (#617)

Co-authored-by: github-actions[bot] <41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Co-authored-by: Vykis <81580355+veekeys@users.noreply.github.com>

chore(deps): Update deps and move resolutions to root (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#668)

Replaced `cpx` with `cpy`, cleaned up and moved resolutions to root.

chore: Move pre-commit hook to root (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#669)

Moved husky and lint-staged dependencies to root package.json. and updated husky to latest version, so config lives in .husky folder instead of in package.json.

Moved copyrightLinter.js into configs package and moved lint:copyright command to root. Also hardcoded fallback pattern in the script itself to fix CI not linting all files.

Root lint-staged config runs prettier and copyright linter because we need those everywhere. itwinui-react workspace overrides root lint-staged config to add eslint to the hook.

chore: Use cypress for storybook visual tests (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#660)

This PR introduces a new apps/storybook workspace dedicated for Storybook and Cypress visual testing.

iTwin/iTwinUI-react#iTwin/iTwinUI-react#iTwin/iTwinUI-react# Storybook

The storybook app is initialized with a minimal vite app and the storybook is built using @storybook/builder-vite instead of webpack. The existing story files are copied over with a few changes (e.g. removing creevey, fixing TS, etc). Also added the Open Sans font.

Storybook can be built using yarn build script and local server with HMR can be started using yarn dev. 

iTwin/iTwinUI-react#iTwin/iTwinUI-react#iTwin/iTwinUI-react# Cypress

Cypress setup follows the traditional "integration testing" route by using cy.visit() on story iframes. The actual visual screenshot testing is done using cypress-image-diff-js. Each story has a corresponding .test.ts file which explicitly lists the story names. Any stories that need to be skipped can simply be excluded from this list.

Test images are currently generated using Electron 94 browser.

iTwin/iTwinUI-react#iTwin/iTwinUI-react#iTwin/iTwinUI-react# Docker

I reused the Dockerfile from iTwinUI-layouts and updated Cypress version. Currently it needs to be built (once) locally using yarn build-docker. The run-tests.js file loads this docker image, and then entrypoint.sh uses serve to start an http server on the built storybook-static folder, before running cypress run.

iTwin/iTwinUI-react#iTwin/iTwinUI-react#iTwin/iTwinUI-react# Misc / unrelated changes

Had to add a check for NaN in useOverflow because there was some division-by-zero happening.

message:
chore: release 0.59.0 (#643)

Co-authored-by: github-actions[bot] <41898282+github-actions[bot]@users.noreply.github.com>
Co-authored-by: Vykis <81580355+veekeys@users.noreply.github.com>

chore: Convert to monorepo (#651)

- Moved all source files into packages/itwinui-css
- Added yarn workspaces + turborepo
- Changed the build slightly to output to css and scss folders and included those in package.json#files.
- This resulted in a change in the stylesheet import in all html files.
- Created shared package to run copyrightLinter from root
- Updated all paths in workflows (confirmed CI passing)

docs: Added `yarn build-docker` to CONTRIBUTING.md (#711)

* Added the `yarn build-docker` command to CONTRIBUTING.md

* Added an alias script command to run `yarn build-docker` from the root folder

* Saved CONTRIBUTING.md without formatting but with `yarn build-docker`

chore: Use vite for build and dev steps (#708)

Added vite v3 as our dev server, so we can run `yarn dev` to preview html files. It's also used for running backstop visual tests on the minified files that get outputted by `vite build`. And it's also hosted on github pages for both branch previews and home page.

Replaced script imports with module imports and added used layer imports to work around a vite bug with css ordering.

chore: Added aliases in root for commands in css package (#778)

Added aliases in root for css package commands: `createComponent`, `approve`, `clean:images`

chore: Update vulnerable `minimatch` and remove unused `cpx` (#795)

Fixes yarn audit.

chore: Create new docs site (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#785)

The code lives in a new workspace called website. This is just an initial version. There are missing features, bugs, and the content is placeholder. But most of the code (excluding content) should be good to keep in the final version.

Co-authored-by: Mayank <mayank99@users.noreply.github.com>
Co-authored-by: Greta <greta.nausedaite@bentley.com>

chore: Remove the need to copy .md files (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#952)

Removed vulnerable dependency on cpy-cli. Instead of copying the .md files from root into package, they now live in the package and are symlinked at the root of the monorepo.

chore: Add nextjs and astro playgrounds (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#951)

Added new folder of isolated playgrounds containing examples of vite, nextjs and astro. Removed shared tsconfig and moved astro prettier config into shared configs Updated contributing guide with urls.

chore: Update resolutions for npm audit (iTwin/iTwinUI-react#990)

- Updated format of deps to point to exact versions. Also updated dev deps format to be less ambiguous.
- Added missing resolutions for `loader-utils` and `minimatch`.

These were done to make it work with `npm install` and `npm audit` (not yarn) in azure pipelines.

chore: Update deps (#857)

Updated deps in preparation of monorepo merge. It's important not to have conflicts especially when it comes to prettier and husky. Husky hook format changed (moved from package.json to .husky folder) and prettier resulted in some formatting changes in vite.config.ts and badge.js. Other than that, everything seems to work the same.

message:
chore: Fix errors in astro workspaces (#929)

Updated backstopjs through which puppeteer got upgraded and no longer requires force resolving node-fetch, so astro is free to use node-fetch v3.

chore: Fix and combine copyright linters (#952)

- moved a combined version of copyrightLinter to scripts, deleted old versions from `shared` and `configs`
- ran yarn lint:copyright which added missing copyright headers to some .js files

upgrade deps and add cra playground (#1083)

updated vite/astro to latest, added CRA playground, and updated README to use a codesandbox link which opens the CRA playground.

replace sandpack with static examples (#1088)

Sandpack comes with a huge bundle and takes forever to load, so I'm replacing it with statically rendered, hydrated examples (they load instantly and are also interactive). For editing, they can be opened in codesandbox externally.

In the process, I also improved a lot of the example code for readability/usability.

The approach for including code examples has now changed. Examples will first need to be exported in src/examples/index.tsx and then used in mdx files manually.
patch storybook vite builder for windows (#1213)

update backstop and use prebuilt docker image (#1259)

Co-authored-by: Greta <83585998+gretanausedaite@users.noreply.github.com>
update cypress to v12 and use prebuilt docker image (#1258)

message: fix dynamic imports in CJS and jest (#1742)

update deps (#1826)

Too many to list them all, but here are the important ones:
- latest version of `turbo`, includes support for auto-loading `env` files
- removed all overrides that are no longer necessary
- removed some unnecessary dependencies like `@emotion/styled`

remove local dependency on changesets (#1833)

`@changesets/cli` will now be automatically installed on-demand using `npx`. Everything should work the same as before, other than maybe a small delay when running changeset commands.

add `loading` prop to `Button` (#2058)

This allows displaying a progress indicator inside a `Button`, without causing layout shift. Only handles visuals for now; a11y to be tackled in a later PR.

New CSS apis introduced: `[data-iui-loading]`, `.iui-button-spinner`, `.iui-button-label`
